Remarks. The male of this new species is similar to that
of Z. flavotegulata
( Chen, 1957 ), but differs from the latter mainly in having metasomal segments 1–3 ferruginous (metasoma wholly black in
Z. flavotegulata
); the tegula blackish-brown (yellowish-brown in
Z. flavotegulata
); in having metasomal tergum 2 with a narrow apical fringe of yellow setae (metasomal tergum 2 posterad with distinct band of appressed white setae in
Z. flavotegulata
); and having flagellomere 1 0.76 × flagellomere 2 length (0.85–0.92 × in
Z. flavotegulata
).
